snippet.textDisplay:
As of march 12, Norway has closed down schools for at least 2 weeks, this does not mean that students have a 2 week break. We still have to work. if possible you should work from home, public gatherings are cancelled for the time being. public transport is still up and running but no interaction with driver. We are adviced not to visit hospitals, elderly and so on to minimize the risk of infection.
And we are at phase 1. and people are going crazy, hoarding everything. lactose intolerant people are stocking up on milk, and people that need insulin might not get everything they need because people are hoarding it. Call me crazy, but I like to believe that the government is doing this to stop the virus from spreading out of control here. and we might even be able to stop it in phase 1. maybe 2. That's just me being optimistic.
